OriginalText:
Hike, climb, and soar through the peaceful mountainside landscapes of Hawk Peak Provincial Park. Follow the marked trails or explore the backcountry as you make your way to the summit. Along the way, meet other hikers, discover hidden treasures, and take in the world around you.

[h2]Key Features[/h2]
[list][*]Explore the island any way you like. Choose your own path to follow and see where it leads you. You never know what you might stumble into!
[*]Hike at your own pace ��� there���s no need to rush to the summit! Take your time fishing along the river banks or swimming by the lakeshore.
[*]Collect hidden treasures to reach new heights. Try taking a dive off the mountain peaks to soar above the forests.
[*]Chat with the other hikers you meet along your route. You might be able to help each other out!
[*]Listen to a lush original soundtrack by Mark Sparling that progresses dynamically as you explore the wilderness.[/list]
Hike, climb, and soar through the peaceful mountainside landscapes of Hawk Peak Provincial Park as you make your way to the summit.

LineText:
es geht um eine uralte Fantasiewelt, in
der Zauberer um Ruhm kämpfen, indem sie Steine
und Felsen in mächtige Golems verwandeln,
die sich in epischen Arenen voller gefährlicher
Fallen und furchterregender Monster bekämpfen.
OriginalText:
it's about an ancient fantasy world where sorcerers
battle for glory by enchanting stones and rocks into
powerful golems that fight each other in epic arenas
filled with perilous traps and fearsome monsters
Speaker: Original

LineText:
und obwohl man auf den ersten Blick denkt,
dass die Kampfszenen im Mittelpunkt stehen,
sind es in Wirklichkeit die Charaktere, die
die Geschichte bestimmen, und alle Kämpfe
sind in gewisser Weise metaphorisch mit internen
Konflikten der einzelnen Zauberer verbunden, die
in einer bösen und gefühllosen Welt
überleben müssen.
OriginalText:
and although the fight sequences seem like
the focus at first it's really the characters
that drive the story and all the battles are
sort of metaphorically tied to each wizard's
internal conflicts as they struggle to survive
in a ruthless and uncaring world
